inline_comments.message:
For instance, all of the getDeployedXxxPolicies methods could be replaced with a single method:

    private <T, R> T getDeployedPolicies(List<ToscaPolicyIdentifier> policyIdentifiers,
                    BiFunctionWithEx<String, String, R> getter, BiConsumer<T, R> consumer,
                    T data) throws PfModelException {

        if (!policyIdentifiers.isEmpty()) {
            for (ToscaPolicyIdentifier policyIdentifier : policyIdentifiers) {
                R result = getter.apply(policyIdentifier.getName(),
                        policyIdentifier.getVersion().split("\\.")[0]);
                consumer.accept(data, result);
            }
        }
        return data;
    }

then it could be invoked like this:

            Map<String, LegacyGuardPolicyOutput> deployedGuardPolicies =
                            getDeployedPolicies(policyIdentifiers, modelsProvider::getGuardPolicy, Map::putAll, new HashMap<>());

That one method could be used in lieu of getDeployedPolicies, getDeployedOpPolicies, and getDeployedGuardPolicies.  A similar thing could be done to replace the constructXxx methods with a single method.  Likewise with the hasXxxPolicyVersion and collectXxx methods.
